  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" Eby Cherian versus Jerema John pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_6_202_209','2025INSC709'); ><font size='4'> <strong>EBY CHERIAN<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>JEREMA JOHN </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 6 S.C.R. 202</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 709</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001882025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Matter pertains to the correctness of the order passed by the High Court upholding the interim custody arrangement made by the family court. Headnotes&dagger; Family law &ndash; Custody of child &ndash; Interim-custody arrangement by the family court &ndash; Challenge to Respondent left the matrimonial home, and since then the child exclusively in her care &ndash; Appellant employed on rotational overseas assignments, filed petition seeking permanent custody of the child, and during pendency sought interim visitation &ndash; Family Court held that as and when the<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 14-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 6924/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Case Partly allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_6_202_209','2025INSC709','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-